F. DE BURE'S BIBLIOGRAPHIE INSTRUCTIVE, WITH ANNOTATIONS BY J.-F. NEE DE LAROCHELLE.DESCRIBES A RECENT IMPORTANT ACQUISITION OF THE BIBLIOTHEQUE NATIONALE ANDDISCUSSES ITS SIGNIFICANCE. THE BIBLIOGRAPHIE INSTRUCTIVE WAS 1ST PUBLISHED IN1584 AS A HANDBOOK FOR COLLECTORS. A BRIEF ACCOUNT IS GIVEN OF THE AUTHOR ANDHIS WORK. NEE DE LA ROCHELLE, A LATE 18TH CENTURY SCHOLAR AND DILETTANTE, USEDHIS COPY AS AN EVERYDAY TOOL. THE VARIOUS TYPES OF NOTES ARE DESCRIBED, ANDTHEIR IMPORTANCE CONSIDERED IN RELATION TO FORMAT, BIBLIOGRAPHICAL REFERENCES,CLASSIFICATION PROCEDURES, POINTS OF LEARNING, AND THE HISTORY OF THE PRINTEDBOOK, AS EVIDENCE FOR THE STUDY OF BIBLIOGRAPHY ON THE EVE OF THE FRENCHREVOLUTION